==Scots==
===Etymology===
{{unk|sco}}; likely imitative. Compare {{m|sco|whang||a blow}}.
===Noun===
{{sco-noun}}
# a sudden [[tug]], a [[jerk]], a yank
# a [[blow]], a [[slap]]
#* {{quote-book|sco|1833|{{w|James Hogg}}|The Brownie of Bodsbeck||51|I took up my neive an’ gae him a '''yank''' on the haffat till I gart his bit brass cap rattle against the wa’.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xCogAAAAMAAJ&pg=RA1-PA51|translation=I raised my fist and gave him a blow on the temple that made his little brass cap rattle against the wall.}}
===Verb===
{{sco-verb}}
# to [[jerk]], to [[pull]] suddenly
# to [[move]] [[quickly]] or in a [[lively]] manner
